methods.getCauses: :return: (java.lang.Throwable[]) all of the exceptions that resulted in this one.
methods.maybeWrapInMultiException:
If there is a single exception, return that exception; otherwise wrap the causes into a MultiException.

*Overload 1*  
  :param description: (java.lang.String) - the description for the MultiException
  :param causes: (java.lang.Throwable...) - the array of causes
  :return: (java.lang.Throwable) a MultiException or the single Throwable
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param description: (java.lang.String) - the description for the MultiException
  :param causes: (java.util.List<java.lang.Throwable>) - the list of causes
  :return: (java.lang.Throwable) a MultiException or the single Throwable
  
*Overload 3*  
  :param description: (java.lang.String) - the description for the MultiException
  :param causes: (java.lang.Exception...) - the array of causes
  :return: (java.lang.Exception) a MultiException or the single Exception

text:
An exception to use when a series of operations must all be executed, but may all throw exceptions themselves. This
 allows for retention of all exception data.
